title: Mac Davis - Thunder in the Afternoon (1977 quad mix 24/96 lossle
description:
Mac Davis - Thunder in the Afternoon (1977 quad/surround mix 24/96 lossless 4.0 DVD-A)

24/96 4.0 lossless MLP (DVD-Audio).
16/48 4.0 DTS @ 1536kbps (DVD-Video) for compatibility with standard DVD players.

Converted from quad SQ encoded vinyl using a FOSGATE RESEARCH TATE II 101A hardware decoder.
 
 
"Singer/songwriter Davis has done more to set back the cause of popular music in the Seventies than any other single figure. His execrable pop-morality pseudo-country hits encouraged a wholesale run to sententious Muzak that makes movie director Robert Altman's vision of Nashville's self-righteousness and pomposity look like humility. His one legitimate claim to rock foot-notoriety was writing 'In the Ghetto' for Elvis" [0 stars]
- John Swenson, Rolling Stone
